<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-26"><hi rend="italic">October 26, 1891</hi>.</date>
                            (Received October 27.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Egan reports that, in replying to his note of the 22d instant, the
                        minister for foreign affairs persists in his refusal to grant the refugees
                        safe-conduct. He considers the discussion closed, and declares the further
                        exchange of notes on the subject useless.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>